description:
**Brian's Report:** "Hamburger is still over the new card button on top right on desktop. For desktop put that hamburger button on top left instead."

**Current Problem:**
Hamburger menu (gear icon) positioned at top right, overlapping "New Card" button on desktop.

**Expected:**
Desktop: Hamburger at top left
Mobile: Can stay where it is (or bottom)

**Fix Required:**

CSS for desktop:
```css
@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .hamburger-menu {
    position: fixed;
    top: 20px;
    left: 20px;  /* Move to left on desktop */
    right: auto;
  }
}
```

**Screenshot proof required:**
MEDIA:./screenshots/android-hamburger.png (current position ok)
MEDIA:./screenshots/iphone-hamburger.png (current position ok)
MEDIA:./screenshots/desktop-hamburger.png (moved to top left, no overlap with New Card)

**Priority:** P1 (High) - UX polish, prevents button overlap

**Brian's Request:** "Display a unique id # for each card task or bug in the top right corner"

**Implementation:**

Each card already has:
- Story Number (US-001, US-002, etc.)
- Internal ID (card-1770521031236, etc.)

Display story number in top right corner of each card:

```html
<div class="card">
  <div class="card-id">#US-042</div>
  <h3>Task Title</h3>
  ...
</div>
```

CSS:
```css
.card-id {
  position: absolute;
  top: 8px;
  right: 8px;
  font-size: 11px;
  color: #64748b;
  font-weight: 600;
  background: rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
  padding: 2px 6px;
  border-radius: 4px;
}
```

**Screenshot proof required:**
MEDIA:./screenshots/android-card-ids.png
MEDIA:./screenshots/iphone-card-ids.png
MEDIA:./screenshots/desktop-card-ids.png

**Priority:** P2 (Medium) - UX improvement, helpful for tracking

**Brian's Report:** "There should be 9 restaurants, there are small restaurant icons but I think those are not your recommendations. Make clear your top ranked breakfast, lunch, dinner recommendations with pins."

**Current Problem:**
Small restaurant icons visible on map are generic Google Maps POIs, NOT the curated recommendations.

**Expected:**
9 clearly visible custom markers for May 8:
- 3 breakfast (Domo Café, Renoir, Yoshinoya)
- 3 lunch (ICHIRAN, Gyukatsu Motomura, etc.)
- 3 dinner (Terakoya, etc.)

**Implementation:**

Use custom marker icons to distinguish recommendation types:

```javascript
// Breakfast - Orange fork/knife icon
const breakfastIcon = {
  path: google.maps.SymbolPath.CIRCLE,
  fillColor: '#FF6B35',  // Orange
  fillOpacity: 1,
  strokeWeight: 2,
  strokeColor: '#fff',
  scale: 12
};

// Lunch - Green fork/knife icon  
const lunchIcon = {
  path: google.maps.SymbolPath.CIRCLE,
  fillColor: '#4ECDC4',  // Teal
  fillOpacity: 1,
  strokeWeight: 2,
  strokeColor: '#fff',
  scale: 12
};

// Dinner - Purple fork/knife icon
const dinnerIcon = {
  path: google.maps.SymbolPath.CIRCLE,
  fillColor: '#9B59B6',  // Purple
  fillOpacity: 1,
  strokeWeight: 2,
  strokeColor: '#fff',
  scale: 12
};

// Or use custom PNG icons:
const breakfastIcon = {
  url: 'data:image/svg+xml;base64,...',  // Custom breakfast icon
  scaledSize: new google.maps.Size(40, 40)
};
```

**Add labels to markers:**

```javascript
new google.maps.marker.AdvancedMarkerElement({
  map,
  position: restaurant.coordinates,
  title: restaurant.name,
  content: createRestaurantMarker(restaurant),
  zIndex: 1000  // Ensure on top
});

function createRestaurantMarker(restaurant) {
  const icon = document.createElement('div');
  icon.className = 'restaurant-marker';
  icon.innerHTML = `
    <div class="marker-pin ${restaurant.category}">
      <span class="marker-label">🍽️</span>
    </div>
    <div class="marker-label">${restaurant.name}</div>
  `;
  return icon;
}
```

**CSS:**

```css
.restaurant-marker {
  position: relative;
}

.marker-pin {
  width: 40px;
  height: 40px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  font-size: 20px;
  box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
}

.marker-pin.breakfast {
  background: #FF6B35;  /* Orange */
}

.marker-pin.lunch {
  background: #4ECDC4;  /* Teal */
}

.marker-pin.dinner {
  background: #9B59B6;  /* Purple */
}

.marker-label {
  background: white;
  padding: 2px 6px;
  border-radius: 4px;
  font-size: 11px;
  font-weight: 600;
  margin-top: 4px;
  white-space: nowrap;
}
```

**Acceptance Criteria:**

Given user views May 8 on trip map
When they zoom to Tokyo area
Then 9 large, distinct markers visible:
- 3 orange (breakfast)
- 3 teal (lunch)
- 3 purple (dinner)
And each marker shows restaurant name on hover
And markers clearly different from Google Maps generic POIs

**Screenshot proof required:**
MEDIA:./screenshots/android-restaurant-markers.png
MEDIA:./screenshots/iphone-restaurant-markers.png
MEDIA:./screenshots/desktop-restaurant-markers.png

All 3 showing 9 distinct colored markers for May 8 restaurants.

**Priority:** P1 (High) - UX clarity, differentiates recommendations from noise
